<item>
            <title>[DERBY-5204] Misplaced p tags in release notes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-5204</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The HTML in the release notes doesn&apos;t pass the tests for HTML 4.01 Transitional at &lt;a href=&quot;http://validator.w3.org&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://validator.w3.org&lt;/a&gt;. The problems are misplaced &amp;lt;p&amp;gt; tags:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) The list of supported Java and JDBC is enclosed in a &amp;lt;p&amp;gt; ... &amp;lt;/p&amp;gt; section. A paragraph cannot contain block-level elements, like unordered lists - &amp;lt;ul&amp;gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2) The section that summarizes issues with release notes contains anchors with paragraphs nested inside them. Paragraphs cannot be nested inside anchors.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12505186">DERBY-5204</key>
