                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13025197" author="knutanders" created="Tue, 26 Apr 2011 13:43:06 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;The attached patch attempts to fix the broken HTML by making these changes:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) Close the paragraph before starting the unordered list in releaseSummary.xml.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2) Changed ReleaseNoteGenerator to use the inline grouping element &amp;lt;span&amp;gt; instead of &amp;lt;p&amp;gt; inside the anchors. The purpose of these &amp;lt;p&amp;gt; tags was just to group some elements together, so &amp;lt;span&amp;gt; sounds like a good match.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With these changes, the release notes that got generated in my environment passed validation for HTML 4.01 Transitional. (They didn&apos;t pass HTML 4.01 Strict, though.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13025201" author="rhillegas" created="Tue, 26 Apr 2011 13:52:42 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, Knut. These changes look good to me. +1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13025211" author="knutanders" created="Tue, 26 Apr 2011 14:16:39 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, Rick!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 1096741. Also back-ported to 10.8 with revision 1096746.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
